---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SchemaMarkup from "../../components/SchemaMarkup.astro";
import Icon from "../../components/Icon.astro";

// Make this page dynamic via SSR
export const prerender = false;

const publishDate = new Date("October 5 2026");
const author = "The Valley Clean Team";
const readTime = "5 min read";

const isPublished = new Date().getTime() >= publishDate.getTime();

// FAQ Schema data for AEO optimization
const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: []
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Preparing Your Guest Room and Bathrooms for Holiday Visitors | The Valley Clean Team"
  description="Make guests feel at home! Follow our expert guide for preparing and deep cleaning your guest rooms and bathrooms before holiday visitors arrive."
  ogImage="https://storage.googleapis.com/msgsndr/iKQIBhpKVL2XVPgU7HMd/media/6920802945dc047d65b4ec5d.png"
>
  <SchemaMarkup
    type="article"
    title="Preparing Your Guest Room and Bathrooms for Holiday Visitors"
    description="Make guests feel at home! Follow our expert guide for preparing and deep cleaning your guest rooms and bathrooms before holiday visitors arrive."
    publishDate="October 5 2026"
    author={author}
  />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-gray-800 to-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-[#FFA985]/20 text-[#FFA985] rounded-full text-sm font-medium mb-6">
          Hosting/Seasonal
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          Preparing Your Guest Room and Bathrooms for Holiday Visitors
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          {isPublished ? "Expert Cleaning Guide" : "Coming October 5 2026."}
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center space-x-4 text-gray-400 mb-8">
          <span>October 5 2026</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>{readTime}</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>By {author}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content Toggle based on Published Date -->
  {isPublished ? (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <!-- TODO: REPLACE THIS SECTION WITH YOUR ACTUAL BLOG CONTENT -->
          <h2>How Can You Prepare Your Guest Room and Bathrooms for Holiday Visitors?</h2>
<p><strong>Preparing your guest room and bathrooms for holiday visitors requires a systematic approach to ensure a welcoming and comfortable environment. Start by thoroughly cleaning and decluttering these spaces, followed by adding thoughtful touches like fresh linens and toiletries. For a stress-free holiday season in The Shoals & Surrounding Areas, consider professional cleaning services to guarantee a pristine experience for your guests.</strong></p>

<h3>Step 1: Declutter and Deep Clean</h3>
<p>Before your guests arrive, eliminate unnecessary items to create a spacious and inviting atmosphere. A clean, uncluttered space sets the foundation for comfort and hospitality.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Declutter:</strong> Remove personal items and excess decor. Clear off surfaces for guest use.</li>
  <li><strong>Deep Clean:</strong> Dust, vacuum, and mop floors. Pay extra attention to corners and under furniture.</li>
  <li><strong>Spotless Bathrooms:</strong> Scrub and disinfect all surfaces, including sinks, toilets, and tubs.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 2: Refresh Linens and Bedding</h3>
<p>There's nothing quite like fresh linens to make your guests feel at home. Ensure all bedding and bathroom linens are freshly laundered and inviting.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Bed Linens:</strong> Use clean, crisp sheets and pillowcases. Consider a cozy throw for added warmth.</li>
  <li><strong>Bathroom Towels:</strong> Provide a set of plush towels for each guest, including hand towels and washcloths.</li>
  <li><strong>Extra Blankets and Pillows:</strong> Store additional blankets and pillows in the closet for guest convenience.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 3: Stock Essential Toiletries</h3>
<p>Anticipate your guests' needs by stocking the bathroom with essential toiletries. This thoughtful gesture ensures they have everything they need.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Shampoo and Conditioner:</strong> Opt for travel-sized bottles or stock full-sized options.</li>
  <li><strong>Soap and Body Wash:</strong> Provide options for personal preference.</li>
  <li><strong>Toothpaste and Toothbrush:</strong> Have spares available in case guests forget theirs.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 4: Add Personal Touches</h3>
<p>Creating a welcoming environment goes beyond cleaning and stocking essentials. Personal touches can make a significant impact.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Fresh Flowers:</strong> A small vase of seasonal flowers can brighten any room.</li>
  <li><strong>Reading Material:</strong> Offer a selection of magazines or books for light reading.</li>
  <li><strong>Welcome Note:</strong> A handwritten note can add a personal touch and express your hospitality.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Step 5: Ensure Comfort and Functionality</h3>
<p>Your guests' comfort is paramount. Ensure the room and bathrooms are functional and meet their needs.</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Lighting:</strong> Check all lighting fixtures and provide bedside lamps for reading.</li>
  <li><strong>Temperature Control:</strong> Ensure the thermostat is adjustable or provide a fan or heater for comfort.</li>
  <li><strong>Wi-Fi Access:</strong> Provide clear instructions for connecting to your home network.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Consider Professional Cleaning Services</h3>
<p>For those in The Shoals & Surrounding Areas, preparing for guests can be stress-free by enlisting professional cleaning services. The Valley Clean Team offers military-precision cleaning and veteran-owned accountability, ensuring a flawless experience for your holiday visitors.</p>

<h3>Reclaim Your Time—Book a Guaranteed Clean with The Valley Clean Team Today</h3>
<p>Why spend your valuable holiday time cleaning when you could be enjoying the season with loved ones? Let our vetted specialists handle the cleaning with precision and care. Our transparent pricing starts at $125, and we guarantee a meticulous clean every time. Call us now to schedule your service and ensure a memorable, stress-free holiday for you and your guests.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  ) : (
    <article class="py-16 bg-white border-t border-gray-100 shadow-inner">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-center">
          <Icon name="clock" class="w-16 h-16 text-[#FFA985] mx-auto mb-6" />
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 mt-0">Article Coming Soon!</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 m-0">This article is locked and scheduled to automatically publish on <br/><strong class="text-gray-800 text-xl">October 5 2026</strong>.<br/>Check back then!</p>
          <div class="mt-12">
            <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-6 py-3 text-lg font-semibold text-white bg-[#FFA985] rounded-full hover:bg-[#ff9a70] transition shadow-md no-underline">
              Back to Blog
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  )}
</BaseLayout>
